<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-05-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-05-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="1053" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1053">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00115A Pacific War/1166:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bern</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-05-16">May 16,
                                    1944</date>.<lb/>[Received May 16—9:52 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>3114. American Interests—Japan. Department’s 554, March 8, 1943.<note n="60" xml:id="d1053fn60">Not printed.</note> Swiss Minister,
                                Tokyo, reports first payment effected 22 Americans [on] Guam. While
                                awaiting receipts which Japanese Government requested obtain,
                                husbands interned Kobe signed promissory notes. Gorgé inquires
                                whether may continue such payments or await assurance recipients
                                received payment.<note n="61" xml:id="d1053fn61">In telegram 1792,
                                    May 23, to Bern, the Department authorized continuation of
                                    payments and requested that Mr. Gorgé make every effort to
                                    obtain receipts (740.00115 Pacific War/1166).</note>
                            </p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Harrison</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>